  "body": "This is actually a long-standing problem, but I had never bothered to upgrade Hardhat to ^2.8.0 yet.\r\n\r\nIt's also easily reproducible, below I will be using:\r\n- `ethers`: `5.5.3`\r\n- `ethereumjs-util`: `7.1.3`\r\n- `hardhat`: `2.7.1` & `2.8.3`\r\n\r\nSo, let's take the ERC20Permit implementation from OZ: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/extensions/draft-ERC20Permit.sol\r\n\r\nAnd let's write a simple test suite for the `permit` function:\r\n```typescript\r\n\tit('permit', async () => {\r\n\t\tconst PERMIT_TYPEHASH = keccak256(toUtf8Bytes('Permit(address owner,address spender,uint256 value,uint256 nonce,uint256 deadline)'));\r\n\r\n\t\tconst nonce = await ERC20Mock.nonces(owner.address);\r\n\t\tconst deadline = ethers.constants.MaxUint256;\r\n\t\tconst domSep = await ERC20Mock.DOMAIN_SEPARATOR();\r\n\t\tconst digest = keccak256(\r\n\t\t\tsolidityPack(\r\n\t\t\t\t['bytes1', 'bytes1', 'bytes32', 'bytes32'],\r\n\t\t\t\t[\r\n\t\t\t\t\t'0x19',\r\n\t\t\t\t\t'0x01',\r\n\t\t\t\t\tdomSep,\r\n\t\t\t\t\tkeccak256(\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tdefaultAbiCoder.encode(\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t['bytes32', 'address', 'address', 'uint256', 'uint256', 'uint256'],\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t[PERMIT_TYPEHASH, owner, spender, value, nonce, deadline]\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t)\r\n\t\t\t\t\t),\r\n\t\t\t\t]\r\n\t\t\t)\r\n\t\t);\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tconst PK = getPrivateKey(PrivateKeys.OWNER, true);\r\n\t\tconst { v, r, s } = ecsign(Buffer.from(digest.slice(2), 'hex'), Buffer.from(PK, 'hex'));\r\n\r\n\t\tawait expect(ERC20Mock.permit(owner.address, spender.address, TEST_AMOUNT, deadline, v, hexlify(r), hexlify(s)))\r\n\t\t\t.to.emit(ERC20Mock, 'Approval')\r\n\t\t\t.withArgs(owner.address, spender.address, TEST_AMOUNT);\r\n\t\texpect(await ERC20Mock.allowance(owner.address, spender.address)).to.eq(TEST_AMOUNT);\r\n\t\texpect(await ERC20Mock.nonces(owner.address)).to.eq(BigNumber.from(1));\r\n\t});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis test suite succeeds with Hardhat <=2.7.1 but fails with Hardhat ^2.8.0. In the latter case, the sig recovered by the contract differs. \r\n\r\n@frangio @alcuadrado @fvictorio ",
